Text: graduate news and notes Dear Graduate Brothers Things have been a little hectic around here lately In the last two weeks we have had Dads Weekend Homecoming and FIJI Run We are all just now getting back into the normal routine There have been many positive things happening around here though Dads Weekend we a huge success except for KState losing to Texas AM All the Dads a great time hanging out with there sons and learning what type of brotherhood we have developed here FIJI Run was also very successful This year it was the same week as homecoming so we chose to run the ball from Lawrence to Manhattan on Monday instead of Friday Between the two chapters we raised over with coming from Chi Deuteron alone Homecoming was a good time as always Our partners werent too much help this year but the Phi Gams represented well and made it as crazy as ever of us will be traveling to William Woods in Fulton MO this weekend for their chartering Three members will be on the initiation team there If anyone is interested in attending the festivities email Terry Meyers at Fraternally Kurt Niebuhr Recording Secretary Perge Get your FREE download of MSN Explorer at
